      "rationale": "N=11 non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw constructs from two production lots tested across two independent laboratories. CMM verification of screw geometry confirmed dimensional conformance. Lot traceability documented in test reports. Sample representativeness level 3 achieved."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of clinically relevant loading scenarios including at minimum two distinct load levels or configurations to bound the COU.",
      "rationale": "ASTM F1717 protocol specifies a single standardized compression-bending configuration at a fixed offset distance. While the protocol is widely accepted for regulatory submissions and the experimental results are internally consistent across both laboratories, only one test condition was employed. Variability in clinical loading environments (patient weight, activity level, implant position) was not systematically explored in the experimental campaign. The team considers the standardized protocol sufficient for comparative validation purposes given the well-characterized nature of the F1717 fixture."
    },
    {
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "FEA boundary conditions and loading replicate experimental fixture geometry and applied forces within documented tolerances.",
      "rationale": "F1717 fixture geometry modeled from engineering drawings. Applied load ramp matches test machine displacement rate (5 mm/min quasi-static). Block offset distance (50 mm) replicated in FEA to within 0.1 mm. Equivalency confirmed by pre-test FEA-experiment alignment check."
